{"actor":{"display":"Evin Tunador","id":"evintunador@gmail.com","type":"human"},"content":{"blocks":[{"text":"Task: Implement re-normalization of preserved `unrecognized` events in the\nconversation-ledger repo. This is the second half of the format-drift roadmap\nitem; the preservation half shipped in 0.5.0 (commit b3943c6).\n\n## Background (read these first)\n- README.md \"Roadmap\" → the \"Format-drift: re-normalization\" bullet describes\n  the goal.\n- docs/WIP_TECHNICAL_DESIGN.md → \"Versioning against harness format changes\"\n  (drift + raw preservation paragraph) and \"Canonical objects\".\n- src/adapters/drift.ts → `unrecognizedDraft()`: how preservation events are\n  shaped today (kind=\"unrecognized\", content={unrecognized_type}, actor system,\n  raw={format,data}, conversation.seq = source line index).\n- src/adapters/claude-code.ts and codex.ts → the capture loops that emit them,\n  and `convertLine()` which turns a native line into a conversation_turn.\n- src/schema.ts → `eventId()` identity subset, KNOWN_KINDS (note \"supersession\"\n  already exists), EventLink (`rel: \"supersedes\"`).\n- src/store.ts → `redactEvent()` is the existing precedent for rewriting a\n  stored note line + appending a companion event; `appendEvents`, `readEvents`.\n\n## Goal\nWhen a newer cledger version has learned to interpret a line type it once\npreserved raw-only, it should turn each stored `unrecognized` event whose\n`raw.data` the current adapter now recognizes into the proper\n`conversation_turn`, and append a `supersession` event linking the two — so\nconsumers stop seeing the raw placeholder and see the interpreted turn instead.\nPreservation of still-unrecognized lines is unchanged.\n\n## Design constraints (do not violate)\n1. Append-only + idempotent. Never delete the `unrecognized` event; supersede\n   it via a `supersession` event with a `links: [{rel:\"supersedes\", target}]`.\n   Re-running re-normalization must be a no-op the second time (dedup by id).\n2. Id fidelity is the crux. The conversation_turn produced from a preserved\n   line MUST get the exact id it would have received had it been captured\n   normally in the first place — otherwise a future live capture of the same\n   session duplicates it instead of deduping. That means re-feeding `raw.data`\n   through the SAME adapter convert path with the SAME seq (stored in\n   conversation.seq), session id, and timestamp handling. Verify this with a\n   test that captures a line under a \"blind\" adapter, then re-normalizes, then\n   captures the same line under the \"seeing\" adapter and asserts one event, not\n   two.\n3. Redaction already happened. The stored raw.data was run through the\n   capture-tier redaction stack at preservation time. Re-normalizing must not\n   re-expose anything; work from the stored (already-redacted) raw.data, and\n   let the new conversation_turn ride the normal appendEvents redaction path\n   too (belt and suspenders — it's idempotent on already-placeholdered text).\n4. Reasoning policy is absolute. Codex `reasoning` payloads are never preserved\n   in the first place, so they can't appear here — but do not add any path that\n   would reconstruct provider-withheld encrypted content.\n5. raw.format tells you which adapter/native version produced the stored line;\n   route each unrecognized event to the adapter that owns its producer.source.\n\n## Suggested shape (confirm before building)\n- A `cledger renormalize` command (and library fn) that: reads events, filters\n  kind===\"unrecognized\", groups by producer.source, asks each adapter \"can you\n  now convert this raw.data at this seq?\", and for hits appends the turn + a\n  supersession event. Detection = the adapter's existing convert returning\n  non-null instead of null.\n- Decide: is this a manual command only, or also auto-triggered on capture when\n  a version bump is detected? Recommend manual-only for v1 (auto-detection of\n  \"the adapter changed\" is its own rabbit hole); note it as a follow-up.\n\n## Done means\n- New/updated tests in src/test/adapter-*.test.ts and/or a new\n  renormalize.test.ts, including the id-fidelity dedup test in constraint 2 and\n  a supersession-link assertion. `npm test` green.\n- README roadmap bullet + docs/WIP_TECHNICAL_DESIGN.md updated to reflect what\n  shipped and what remains (auto re-normalization if you defer it).\n- package.json version bump (0.5.0 → 0.6.0), following the repo's linear\n  release-commit-on-main convention. Do not commit or push unless asked.\n\nBefore writing code, lay out your plan and the open design decisions (esp. the\nmanual-vs-auto question and exactly how you reconstruct the turn id) for\nconfirmation.","type":"text"}],"role":"user"},"context":{"branch":"main","cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","dirty_fingerprint":"40d55b341fe9bc7bb7c98026cc92e070c2507c8743cb8cbc39e5efba80fa4f4f","head":"b3943c6ad5883e9299229fc58b73bf4f512f9244","repo":"git@github.com:evintunador/conversation-ledger.git"},"conversation":{"id":"claude-code:b9cb2f57-c42d-4fba-a3e5-4675b5c53898","seq":13},"id":"ev1-ee61843f024029e6f3b7629a4bff37b1fd88605006ef6f3ff20d3ee74d36f5de","kind":"conversation_turn","occurred_at":"2026-07-20T16:55:45.350Z","producer":{"session_id":"b9cb2f57-c42d-4fba-a3e5-4675b5c53898","source":"claude-code","tool":"cledger","version":"0.6.0"},"raw":{"data":{"cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","entrypoint":"cli","gitBranch":"main","isSidechain":false,"message":{"content":"Task: Implement re-normalization of preserved `unrecognized` events in the\nconversation-ledger repo. This is the second half of the format-drift roadmap\nitem; the preservation half shipped in 0.5.0 (commit b3943c6).\n\n## Background (read these first)\n- README.md \"Roadmap\" → the \"Format-drift: re-normalization\" bullet describes\n  the goal.\n- docs/WIP_TECHNICAL_DESIGN.md → \"Versioning against harness format changes\"\n  (drift + raw preservatio