{"actor":{"id":"claude-opus-4-8","type":"agent"},"content":{"blocks":[{"text":"I now have a complete picture. Here's my plan and the key design decisions before I build.\n\n## Plan\n\n**The id-reconstruction mechanism (constraint 2, the crux)**\n\nEach adapter already has a private `convertLine()` that a live capture uses. Re-normalization re-feeds the stored `raw.data` back through that *same* function with the *same* identity-determining inputs, so the produced `conversation_turn` gets the byte-identical id a live capture would have produced:\n\n- **claude-code**: `convertLine(raw.data, event.conversation.seq, version, identity)`. `occurred_at` = `line.timestamp` (recoverable from `raw.data`; timestampless lines can't convert — `convertLine` returns null — so they simply stay preserved). `session_id`/conversation come straight from the line.\n- **codex**: `convertLine(raw.data, event.conversation.seq, sessionId, baseTime, version, identity)` where `sessionId = event.producer.session_id` and `baseTime = event.occurred_at`. When the line has its own timestamp, `convertLine` ignores `baseTime`; when it doesn't, the preserved event's `occurred_at` *is* the `baseTime` a seeing live-capture would compute from the same rollout filename — so either way `occurred_at` matches.\n\nDetection = `convertLine` returns non-null. I'll expose a thin `renormalizeUnrecognized(event, identity)` wrapper from each adapter (keeping the session/baseTime reconstruction knowledge inside the adapter that owns it) rather than exporting `convertLine` raw.\n\n**New `src/renormalize.ts`** — `renormalize(repo)`:\n1. `readEvents`, build `supersededTargets` (from existing `supersession` links) and `existingIds` (all ids across all anchors — guards the cross-anchor duplicate case).\n2. For each `kind===\"unrecognized\"` not already superseded: route by `producer.source` to its adapter. If it converts, produce the turn draft + a deterministic `supersession` draft (`links:[{rel:\"supersedes\",target}]